'''冰圈'''（或稱'''冰盤'''），是一種在水中缓慢旋转的圓形薄冰片，一般認為形成於[[渦旋|渦旋]]中。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.innovateus.net/content/what-are-ice-circles |title=存档副本 |access-date=2016-10-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106000718/http://www.innovateus.net/content/what-are-ice-circles |archive-date=2017-01-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>冰圈通常於[[斯堪的纳维亚|斯堪的纳维亚半岛]]和[[北美洲|北美洲]]出現，但它们偶尔也會在如[[英格兰|英格兰]]和[[威爾士|威尔士]]等較南部的地區被觀察到（如：2008年的威尔士、和2009年的英格兰所观察到的冰圈）。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/weather/article5511931.ece|title=Ice disc brings touch of Scandinavia to Devon river|date=14 January 2009|work=Times Online|publisher=[[The_Times|The Times]]|accessdate=22 April 2010}}</ref><ref name="DailyMail20090113">{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1114071/Ice-Walker-discovers-10ft-wide-spinning-frozen-circle-British-waters-time.html|title=Ice one! Walker discovers 10ft-wide, spinning frozen circle in British waters for the first time|last=David Derbyshire|date=13 January 2009|work=Mail Online|publisher=Daily Mail|accessdate=2009-01-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/earth/4227030/Spinning-ice-disc-phenomenon-seen-in-British-river-for-first-time.html|title=Spinning ice disc phenomenon seen in British river for first time|date=13 January 2009|work=Telegraph.co.uk|publisher=Telegraph Media Group Limited|accessdate=22 April 2010|archive-date=2014-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140105042621/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/earth/4227030/Spinning-ice-disc-phenomenon-seen-in-British-river-for-first-time.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

在2013年的12月，[[北达科他州|北达科他州]]的{{le|夏延河|Sheyenne River}}出現了冰圈。 而在2014年的1月，一個直徑约1.5公尺的冰圈於[[紐約|紐約]]的[[哈德遜河|哈德遜河]]被拍下了照片。  另外，在[[爱达荷州|爱达荷州]]，极端的天气导致[[斯内克河|斯內克河]]於2014年1月也形成了冰圈。 <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.recordonline.com/article/20140123/NEWS/140129847 |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2016-10-05 |archive-date=2016-10-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005201117/http://www.recordonline.com/article/20140123/NEWS/140129847 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

作為一種不寻常的自然现象，冰盘形成於缓慢移动的水、和寒冷的气候中。而一般觀察到的冰圈，雖然大小有些差異，但直径一般都超过15公尺。<ref>Daniel Ostler [http://my.news.yahoo.com/video/rare-sighting-ice-disk-idaho-104748782.html news.yahoo.com] {{Wayback|url=http://my.news.yahoo.com/video/rare-sighting-ice-disk-idaho-104748782.html |date=20140131024004 }}, [http://www.recordonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20140123%2FNEWS%2F140129847 recordonline.com] {{Wayback|url=http://www.recordonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20140123%2FNEWS%2F140129847 |date=20170808195949 }}</ref><ref>Blake Nicholson, [http://bigstory.ap.org/article/unusual-ice-circle-forms-north-dakota-river Unusual ice circle forms in North Dakota river] {{Wayback|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/unusual-ice-circle-forms-north-dakota-river |date=20141211151419 }}, November 26, 2013, Associated Press</ref><ref>Pete Thomas, [http://www.grindtv.com/outdoor/outposts/post/giant-spinning-ice-circle-discovered-in-north-dakotas-sheyenne-river/ Giant spinning ice circle discovered in North Dakota’s Sheyenne River] {{Wayback|url=http://www.grindtv.com/outdoor/outposts/post/giant-spinning-ice-circle-discovered-in-north-dakotas-sheyenne-river/ |date=20150125112952 }}, November 26, 2013, GrindTV</ref>
